<dl id="n06146h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06146h">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06146h"> 146(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ lame excuse that they were / only trying to open a / bottle of stout by hammering / it against the gate ~ <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n06146h"><li>FW 63.30ff </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n06146h">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n06146h">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n06146h">MS BL 47471b-5v</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:152 <a name="c20d" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#c20d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/c20d.htm#n06146h">Draft: I.3&sect;2.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[THE &ldquo;EXPLANATION&rdquo; / Novel Way of Opening a Bottle of Stout.]</font>: The Lord Chief Justice (to the police witness) <br>&mdash; I suppose you know how to draw the cork out of a bottle of stout (a laugh). <br>&ldquo;Yes,&rdquo; replied the witness. <br>The Lord Chief Justice: <mark>Was the sound you heard like trying to get the cork out of a bottle?</mark> <br>Witness: Nothing like it (laughter). <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> <br>Lord Chief Justice: Trying to open a bottle of porter would not rouse you <font color="green">[Behan]</font> from your sleep? <br>Witness: I don&apos;t think so (laughter). <small> <a name="FJ21nov23" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FJ21nov23"><cite title="source">Freeman's Journal</cite></a> (21 November 1923) 9/7</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
